node.text:
Hyped to see see @CarmeloAnthony come to the @lakers! 

Here’s a story about this #throwback video from #defineyourself 2014!

 @Times10 was building, but we hadn’t landed any big clients yet- my good friend @whoischristianvazquez introduced us to Melo - and he took a chance on us!

A small budget, and an hour to shoot- my partner @mistermichaeladrian and I knew we had to go all out.

At this point, people still hadn’t grasped the full scope of Melo’s insane work ethic, and we really wanted to give the world a glimpse. He is the real deal.

Melo allowed 2 hustlers a shot! We are forever grateful, and even after all these years - it’s still one of my favorite pieces.

Adidas team: @Luciodallag @d_rose_city @nickcadam

node.text:
PLEASE WATCH & SHARE 
One of my closest friends @eric_kelly who I have watched him make content that pushes real change! He directed this incredible piece! Please read his caption below:

A Message to the Swing States - From Noam Chomsky.

Trump is a literal fascist waging a war on truth, decency, our planet, and on working people. If Biden wins, we’ll be at his door on day one, demanding the kinds of structural reforms that advance racial, economic, and environmental justice.

"It doesn’t matter how I feel. It doesn’t matter whether you like Biden or not. That's your personal feelings, irrelevant, nobody cares about that. What they care about is what happens to the world." -Noam Chomsky 

Personally, to say collaborating with Noam Chomsky is a dream come true is an understatement. Thanks to everyone in the video, all of the activists and organizers that are out in the streets every damn day, and lastly, thanks everyone who made this happen. 

Let's #VoteTrumpOut

node.title: A Message to the Swing States - Noam Chomsky

node.text:
3 years ago we were tapped by @adidashoops to help tell the story of Legacy, a youth driven initiative focussed on community and empowerment. We got to spend time with coaches, players, and the teams at high schools in both LA and NYC. This story is bigger than basketball.
-
This is why social media is so powerful and so important. For all the bad out there, remember that there’s still so much good- and so many stories to tell. -
What will your Legacy be?

To get where you want to be in your career it is necessary stay true to your goals, improve everyday and more importantly, to be resilient! You need to grind day in, day out to stand out from the pack! LETS GO! 👊

node.text:
Hyped to see see @CarmeloAnthony come to the @lakers! 

Here’s a story about this #throwback video from #defineyourself 2014!

 @Times10 was building, but we hadn’t landed any big clients yet- my good friend @whoischristianvazquez introduced us to Melo - and he took a chance on us!

A small budget, and an hour to shoot- my partner @mistermichaeladrian and I knew we had to go all out.

At this point, people still hadn’t grasped the full scope of Melo’s insane work ethic, and we really wanted to give the world a glimpse. He is the real deal.

Melo allowed 2 hustlers a shot! We are forever grateful, and even after all these years - it’s still one of my favorite pieces.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Ben Ricciardi in Los Angeles/Hollywood California with @fiftyclicks. May be an image of 1 person, beard, standing and outdoors.

node.text: What’s your biggest passion?! Mine has been golf since I was 11. It’s an incredible escape. I was a kid in a candy store going to @pxg in Arizona and getting fitted. What an experience. The people at #pxg are amazing and the clubs are top notch!
